               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160918-149-person1075">
                  ANN 
                  BRAND
               <interp inst="t18160918-149-person1075" type="surname" value="BRAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160918-149-person1075" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160918-149-person1075" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The two prisoners came into the shop both together, on the 12th of September, at eleven o'clock; Robinson asked for a pair of shoes; he was very troublesome in fitting, and I saw Allen cramming something into his bosom. I looked in his bosom, and saw a pair of shoes with the heels upwards. I took them from him, and called my husband, as I thought he had more in his bosom. Before my husband could come, he ran away; Robinson sat quietly in the chair.</p>
               <p>ABRAMAM JOEL. I went after him, and brought him back; and he threw the shoes away; I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>ROBINSON. <rs id="t18160918-149-verdict785" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18160918-149-verdict785" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 44.</p>
